If you are looking to hit the slopes this season, you may be trying to opt for good timing and the best snowfall. Here are a few pointers for choosing the best skiing weather.

Aim For Powder: Whether you are a beginner or a seasoned professional, fresh powder makes for ideal skiing conditions. Snow that has just fallen, or powder, can make for a soft landing, and it can also make for amazing scenery. Powder makes great skiing conditions at any level, and you can anticipate snowfall with your weather app. Android and iPhone weather apps can provide you with local radar weather information that will ensure you can be one of the first to enjoy fresh snowfall.

Keep Temperatures Cool: You want the weather to be cool- at least below thirty degrees- to avoids slush. Again, you can rely on your weather app, Android, or iPhone, to ensure that you are setting out to ski in optimal conditions.

Opt For Sun: A sunny day is ideal for skiing. Now only will you fair visibility, but you’ll also be able to enjoy the view. Conversely, you want to avoid a blizzard, as this can provide for unsafe skiing conditions, even if you are an expert. A quick look at your weather app will alert you of any incoming storms so that you can avoid the danger, and instead, spend your afternoon in a hot tub.

Whether you are traveling to a ski resort to relax with friends and family, or to get some serious skiing in, you can rely on your weather app to help you determine optimal skiing conditions.
